snippet.title: Cemil Bayik: an interview with Turkey's most wanted man - BBC News

localized.description:
The BBC has met with Cemil Bayik, leader of Kurdish separatist group the PKK, which is waging simultaneous conflicts against Turkey and so-called Islamic State. Mr Bayik said the PKK is open to negotiations with Turkey, but without such peace talks the decades-long conflict will continue.
He also confirmed the the PKK has had "direct" communications with the United States in the battle against so-called Islamic State.
